        <updateDate>2020-11-19T19:08:26Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Medigap Consumer Protection Act of </strong><b>2019</b></p> <p>This bill modifies several provisions with respect to Medigap policies (Medicare supplemental health insurance policies) and other requirements under Medicare.</p> <p>Among other things, the bill (1) expands guaranteed issue rights with respect to Medigap policies, which require that a policy be offered to any eligible applicant without regard to health status; and (2) establishes an annual cost-sharing limit under Medicare of $5,500 beginning in 2022, with annual adjustments thereafter.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
